Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.04,0:00:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.02,0:00:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.55,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.72,0:01:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Having emerged victorious in the Battle of Midway \Nand gained the upper hand, the US Navy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.50,0:01:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was planning to make use of that momentum \Nto seize the initiative in the Pacific War for good,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.02,0:01:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and was about to launch \Na major counterattack against Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.85,0:02:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,August 6th, 1942. \NA convoy of 31 ships, carrying 19,000 Marines,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.70,0:02:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,protected by an escort fleet of approximately 60 ships, \Nwith three aircraft carriers and one battleship as its core,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.54,0:02:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was sneaking north through the South Pacific.{/secretly heading}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.21,0:02:19.04,Sign,,0,0,300,,{\b1\bord0\blur1\fade(1000,0)\c&HE1E1D3&}Episode 13 \N{\fs80}First Battle of the Solomon Islands {doesn't say islands so I'm unsure if that's the right wording}{第1次ソロモン海戦}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.03,0:02:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of capturing Tulagi and Guadalcanal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.27,0:02:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is primarily to ensure a safe corridor \Nbetween the United States and Australia. {/establish a connection}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.24,0:02:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, it will serve as a foothold \Nfor the subsequent capture of Rabaul. {/become a stepping stone in gaining total control (of people or counties); suppression; oppression; control; mastery; ascendancy; supremacy over rabaul}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.03,0:02:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirdly,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.19,0:02:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it will curb any further Japanese expansion south.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,As the recon aircraft reports, \Nthe Japanese airfield under construction at Guadalcanal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.11,0:02:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't received a single plane yet. {I feel that there's a special word in English for receiving planes}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.77,0:02:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But they can always send some from Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.77,0:02:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we have the Coastwatchers \Nfrom the {Royal }Australian Navy Intelligence{ Department} for. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coastwatchers}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.87,0:02:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To be precise, these "Coastwatchers" were the civilians, \Nmobilized to defend the vast Australian coast -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.35,0:03:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,farmers, pastors, government officials, miners, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.69,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They mixed in with the local tribes, \Nlurking in the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They were tasked with providing hour-by-hour intel \Non the movements of the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.61,0:03:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance from Rabaul \Nto Tulagi and Guadalcanal is about 560 nautical miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.39,0:03:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,With the range of the enemy planes in mind, \Nthey'd only be able to harass us from above {lit: exist in our sky - I hope he means this - 敵機の性能上から見て我々の上空にいるのはせいぜい20分か30分足らずに過ぎないのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,for 20 or 30 minutes at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it will take our troops \Nfour days at least to complete the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.81,0:03:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we do if the enemy attacks in waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Our side had already lost Lexington in the Coral Sea \Nand Yorktown at Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What would we do if we lose any more flattops?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.05,0:03:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Flattops are vulnerable to bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As the commanding officer in charge of landing, \NI cannot send some 20,000 Marines to their death!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We need cover from a flattop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.92,0:03:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm speaking not just as the commanding officer \Nin charge of the Carrier Task Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.89,0:04:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lose two more of our three remaining flattops \Nin the Pacific... No, if we lose even one, the war is lost too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, just cancel this operation altogether!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You go tell that to Admiral Nimitz in Hawaii, \Nor Vice Admiral Ghormley. { In early May, Vice Admiral Ghormley conferred with Admiral Nimitz at Pearl Harbor and then, on May 17, moved to Naval Base Noumea at Nouméa, New Caledonia, to assume his new command.[17]}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, no need to get so worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation has started already.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.92,0:04:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, why don't we carry out \Nthe landing operation as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.48,0:04:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and reconsider things later, \Nif the situation so warrants? {/depending on how it goes}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.68,0:04:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I just try not to think too much \Nabout what comes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not some Tarzans. \NHow are we supposed to fight these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.79,0:04:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese soldiers can dive for miles underwater \Nwhile breathing air through reed stalks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.18,0:05:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Barefoot or in rubber-bottomed sandals, \Nthey can sneak through the jungle silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.17,0:05:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They can climb trees like monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.09,0:05:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They're terribly cunning,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.43,0:05:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and thanks to their spartan lifestyle, \Nthey can travel much farther than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They can survive on measly rations \Nand endure any pain, no matter how severe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I'm scared too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.48,0:05:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They're no ordinary humans. \NWerewolves, if anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.71,0:05:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,August 7th, 3:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.52,0:05:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Northwest of Guadalcanal Island, \Nthe American convoy was approaching Cape Esperance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Protected by an escort fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.33,0:05:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it split into two groups, enveloping Savo Island, \Nsitting at the entrance to a narrow strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.89,0:05:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They were approaching Lunga Point on Guadalcanal \Nand Tulagi on Florida Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.59,0:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the construction of a Japanese airfield \Non Guadalcanal was completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.19,0:06:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, our Guadalcanal airfield is expecting the arrival \Nof the 6th Fighter Air Group from Rabaul. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/6th_Air_Group - not sure where to stick "fighter" in there}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.60,0:06:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The transfer of land-based attack aircraft \Nfrom Misawa Air Group is also scheduled. {not sure what to make of shinshitsu: 陸航機隊が進出してくることになっておる} {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misawa_Air_Group}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.97,0:06:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, the airfield construction team \Nwill conduct rifle training. Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.45,0:06:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Good! At ease! {no clue what's last word, was "go" in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.16,0:06:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, the Japanese garrison on Guadalcanal {lit: defense force }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.75,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,was comprised of about 2,000 construction workers \Nand 230 soldiers of the landing force. {could be 203 but unlikely}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, there were also about 700 Japanese troops in Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.01,0:06:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The American-Australian fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,shelled the seaplane bases on Guadalcanal \Nand Tulagi on Florida Island prior to the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.51,0:06:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Headquarters expected \Nthat the US Army's counterattack,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.69,0:06:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with consideration to its initial operating capacity, \Nwould come in the latter half of 1943. {https://jisho.org/word/%E8%BB%8D%E4%BA%8B%E5%8A%9B}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.03,0:06:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,500)}However, the counteroffensive started sooner than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When this news came \Nto the Japanese air base at Rabaul...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.34,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We should immediately dispatch our entire air force \Nand counterattack the enemy landing party! {was looking for an  antonym to the word "to ground [a plane]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the enemy's plan is either a probing attack, \Nor the destruction of the airfield. {lit: reconnaissance forced attack; risk-taking attack; aggressive attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.29,0:07:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy at point-blank range. \NDefending telegraph room to the last. {assuming last part to be 電信室死守する}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.11,0:07:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Schedule 2nd Air Wing with 27 land-based bombers {added bombers}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.73,0:07:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and 1st Air Wing with 18 Zero fighters \Nfor departure at 07:30. {unsure he means this, just "0730 takeoff"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.79,0:07:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,3rd Air Wing with 9 naval bombers \Nshould depart as soon as it's ready! {no clue what's kanbaku here, assumed it's an abbreviation: kan(ship)baku[hatsu](explosion); just "aircraft" in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.79,0:07:49.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)\c&H06121B&\3c&H8BA399&}Eighth Fleet Headquarters {第八艦隊司令部}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.61,0:07:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the 8th Fleet{ within the Combined Fleet} under the command of Vice Admiral Mikawa, {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/8th_Fleet_(Imperial_Japanese_Navy)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.63,0:07:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,newly established after the Battle of Midway, \Nwas also about to head out for Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.99,0:08:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance from Rabaul to Guadalcanal \Nis about the same as from Tokyo to Shimonoseki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't rely on support from the air force
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, our fleet has also just been formed and \Ndoesn't have a single serious naval maneuver under its belt. {he advocating for not dispatching the fleet to intercept the landings here}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.82,0:08:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And because the distance is so great, {there's a considerable chance that }we might \Ncome under attack from enemy aircraft while on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We should go there fully prepared for that too. {/accepting}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.04,0:08:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since the Battle of Midway, \Nour navy has been scared out of their wits. {no clue what's shougi here, believing HA's "too cowardly"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.45,0:08:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Secretary Yamamoto's opinion? {secretary (government); director; chief - remember that isoroku yamamoto was basically prime minister at this point}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.67,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No objections. {tacit approval; tacit permission; connivance; acquiescence; toleration; overlooking}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.85,0:08:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I'm opposed to the decision \Nof Imperial Headquarters and Combined Fleet command,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.10,0:08:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I intend to carry out this operation within the scope of the discretionary operational freedom delegated to our fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral, we're doing it, aren't we? {secretary (government); director; chief - again choukan, kinda like the universal name for the "commander"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, Staff Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Vice Admiral is resolved, \NI can't voice any protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:08:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Please decide on our further steps depending on the results \Nof the aerial reconnaissance and enemy attacks. {基地航空隊の偵察及び攻撃の成果により後の行動を決めてください - unsure what he means, probably "when our base's air corps is airborne and conducts recon"; also just "attacks", may be enemy's, may be theirs}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.15,0:09:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.46,0:09:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior Staff Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have not yet sailed the surface of that sea even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, it'll be a violent operation. \NWe can't help but to conduct it violently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.63,0:09:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. This would become the first night battle of fleets \Nin the history of naval warfare. We'll do it violently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.31,0:09:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the flagship with all the senior staff, \Nas well as the 6th Air Group to sortie immediately. {no clue what's choukai here, assumed "chou(officer)kai(assembly)" but it's not in dictionary}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Japanese side, the loss of Guadalcanal
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.34,0:09:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,would mean a serious threat \Nfor the security of the New Guinea area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,24 torpedo and conventional bombers \Nheading towards Tulagi and Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.40,0:10:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This intel was then sent to the headquarters \Nof the Pacific Fleet in Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.78,0:10:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And with powerful transmitters, rerouted to the US Task Force, operating off the coast of Guadalcanal, alerting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.30,0:10:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,At noon, we expect an attack on this ship \Nfrom 24 enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.08,0:10:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To the right, above us. Enemy aircraft!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.42,0:11:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.85,0:11:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The damage suffered by the Japanese side \Nin this battle was as follows:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.09,0:11:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,5 land-based bombers, 5 carrier-based bombers, \Nplus two crashed Zero fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.57,0:11:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The American-Australian losses were
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,11 fighters, one dive bomber, \Nplus severe beating sustained by the destroyer USS Jarvis. {was "McMaid in HA, doesn't make sense, there was never such a destroyer, but I found this: "During the landing operations on 7 and 8 August, Japanese naval aircraft based at Rabaul, under the command of Yamada Sadayoshi, attacked the Allied amphibious forces several times, setting afire the transport USS George F. Elliott (which sank two days later) and heavily damaging the destroyer USS Jarvis.[41]" - seems like a mistake on the part of Japanese, but since nobody cares or gonna factcheck, feel free to replace with McMaid or whatever sounds realistic; the closest I could find on https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guadalcanal_naval_order_of_battle is McKean}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.13,0:12:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy aircraft carrier is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.46,0:12:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be prepared \Nto repel at least one enemy aircraft raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.55,0:12:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.98,0:12:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't have a carrier on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We risk total annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.70,0:12:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we can't let the enemy discover us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A surprise attack is our only way forward. {/to defeat the enemy}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.65,0:12:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy patrol forward-to-right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.38,0:12:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, make it seem as if we're heading northwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.40,0:12:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Full to starboard! Hurry! {no clue what's mikaji here, was "full to port" in HA, but if they're going from Rabaul south, it'd make sense to turn right to pretend to head northwest, not left}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.80,0:12:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy patrol plane no longer in sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, restore the normal course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.36,0:13:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.49,0:13:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I need the rest of you to gather in the briefing room! {/operations}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.82,0:13:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.52,0:13:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We escaped the Bougainville Strait and are about \Nto infiltrate the central waterway at high speed. {/breaking through}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.90,0:13:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We're entering it through the right of Savo Island.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:17.90,0:13:21.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fade(0,2000)\blur1\bord0\c&H08121D&\3c&HBDBBB4&\frz-42\move(1000,300,150,-250,0,3600)}Solomon Archipelago \N\N\N\N\N\N{\frz-1}Bougainville Island                                                           \h \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                     Isabel Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                                                                  {\frz-2}Malaita Island \N \h                                                                                                Tulagi \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                    {\frz-3}Guadalcanal Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                                                                             San Cristobal Island
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.17,0:13:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we'll deal a surprise blow to the ships \Ncurrently moored in Guadalcanal,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:20.17,0:13:26.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(2000,0)\q2\blur1\bord0\c&H08121D&\3c&HBDBBB4&\frz-3}\N\N\NIsabel Island                                                  \h \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                               Malaita Island \N\N\N\N\N\N \h {\frz}Tulagi \N\N\NSavo Island                                           \h \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NGuadalcanal Island                                                                                              \h
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.67,0:13:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,following it up with an attack on the enemy in Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.91,0:13:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll quickly withdraw to a point \Nwhere we'll be unreachable by the enemy planes. {/can't attack us}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.55,0:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy patrol aircraft! \N90 degrees to the right and approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.79,0:13:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,3 cruisers, 3 destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.19,0:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,2 seaplane tenders. \NCourse - 120 degrees. Speed 15 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.80,0:14:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is persistent...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd like to change course once again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes too much time. Harass them with the 8-inch guns, \Nsince it doesn't matter at this point. {unsure what he means by "because I don't care" - prolly means "I don't mind spending shells on it"} {/threaten/scare away}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.16,0:14:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, we can be sure that the enemy planes \Nwill show up in a couple of hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.13,0:14:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chokai, Aoba, Kako, Kinugasa, Furutaka - \Norder each heavy cruiser to launch their patrol seaplanes. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Savo_Island_order_of_battle#Japanese_order_of_battle}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigate the enemy position. \NOrder each ship to be on the lookout for enemy aircraft. {lit: maintain a strict anti-aircraft lookout}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.11,0:15:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the scout plane from the Royal Australian Air Force who spotted the Japanese fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,continued to scout the area assigned to it even after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.62,0:15:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And at around 14:30, it returned to its home base \Nin Milne Bay on the southern tip of New Guinea. {not sure what's ittan here}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.21,0:15:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From there its crew reported to Townsville \Nand to MacArthur's Headquarters in Australia {act. says "mcarthur's HQ in Townsville" but he never was there, it was just an important air base, but mcarthur's HQ was in Brisbane then in Port Moresby}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.52,0:15:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the composition of the unidentified Japanese fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.77,0:15:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Which translated into a delay of nearly 8 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.46,0:16:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like we're doing all right so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.25,0:16:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I ever had a day \Nthat's been as long as this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We can now be sure of our victory tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Listen to my directives. {instruction; direction; briefing}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Directive: as per the tradition of our Imperial Navy, \Nwe'll only be contented with a decisive victory in the field! {lit: have a mind for ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.61,0:16:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When we plunge into the battle, \NI need everyone to be calm and collected. {was "night battle" in HA, but I only hear "rushing into; breaking into; storming"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you to do your very best! {/exhaust your power}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.73,0:16:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Telegram to Admiral Ghormley.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Our mission of supporting the landings is concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Our mission of supporting the landings is concluded."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.10,0:17:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost 21 out of our 99 carrier-based aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.58,0:17:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Lost 21 out of our 99 carrier-based aircraft."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,On account of enormous quantity \Nof enemy torpedo and conventional bombers present,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.03,0:17:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the immediate withdrawal of our fleet \Nseems the most appropriate to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.62,0:17:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, we're running short on fuel. I request that \Na refueling ship is dispatched our way as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.20,0:17:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, they had enough fuel to operate for 4 more days.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, the American escort fleet, \Nwhich included an aircraft carrier, withdrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Fletcher, having previously lost \Nthe aircraft carriers Lexington and Yorktown
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.02,0:17:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,during the Battle of the Coral Sea and the Battle of Midway,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.09,0:17:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was now unwilling to accept responsibility \Nfor the potential loss of any more carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.23,0:18:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from Aoba's recon aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.67,0:18:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Three enemy cruisers. \NPatrolling the sea southwest of the Savo Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.75,0:18:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.37,0:18:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, at a speed of 30 knots \Nand a course of 95 degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.66,0:18:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll dash towards the berth in Guadalcanal Island. {anchorage (area); moorage; roadstead ... rapid progress; radical progress}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.87,0:18:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,10 degrees to the right! \NThree cruisers. Proceeding to the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Copy that! {was "illumination" in HA but I only hear "sousa" (is that so?), tho I might be wrong}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.07,0:18:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for night battle! {no clue what's first word, kinda hear migi (right) but doesn't make sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.69,0:18:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to launch! {no clue about a single word, was missing in HA as well, first word is kinda hassha (launch), second is kinda like hajime (begin)}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Return fire! Fire! {guess, no clue what's first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.37,0:19:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,10 minutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.25,0:19:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our grand victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.94,0:19:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn sharply to the left. \NMount a surprise attack on the enemy troops in Tulagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack! Attack! {no clue what he means by "charge; rush; dash; assault; attack", maybe "return fire"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Current time is 00:10. \NTell me frankly what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We must withdraw immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.04,0:21:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're running low on torpedoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.02,0:21:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, the enemy task force is near San Cristobal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.90,0:21:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a question of distance and time? {he's not actually asking but idk what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.09,0:21:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we rush it to the utmost, it would take us two hours \Nto reorganize the fleet and reach Lunga Point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun rises over the Solomon Archipelago after 4 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.04,0:21:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be impossible to escape the enemy carrier's retaliation. {hope he means this: 敵空母から逃れることは不可能です - maybe he means now, maybe "... would be impossible to run away from after 4am"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.55,0:21:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hours, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy transport fleet \Nshould be completely exposed now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.11,0:21:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.64,0:21:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're discovered by an enemy carrier, \Nwe'll be annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.26,0:22:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdraw all formations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.01,0:22:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Course 320 degrees. Speed 30 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.24,0:22:30.26,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\b1\q2\fade(0,000)\blur0.7\bord0\c&HE1E2E3&\3c&HBDBBB4&\move(720,15,560,-680,4000,7000)}\N\N\N\NIsabel Island                                          \h \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                            Malaita Island \N\N{\frz-1}Tulagi  \h \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\frz-2\c&HD7E4EC&}Guadalcanal Island                                          \h \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                     San Cristobal Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                      Rennel Island
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.75,0:22:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But at that time, the American aircraft carrier was trying \Nto get as far away from Guadalcanal Island as she could.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.72,0:22:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral, let's attack once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.04,0:22:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If Chokai goes there alone, \Nshe'll have enough time to escape. {距離から行っても十分に逃げてれます - no clue what he means by "going from the distance", prolly "attacking from the distance" but I couldn't fit it in reasonable CPS anyway}{chokai is his flagship btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.18,0:22:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,By leaving the convoys intact, we're giving the enemy \Na chance to lick his wounds, Vice Admiral! {lit: the enemy will only get fatter/well-off}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.20,0:22:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you considered the effect of that \Non future operations? {lit: if the enemy gets fat, the operations after this...}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.01,0:23:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't afford losing \Nan important warship in a reckless attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.30,0:23:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the first night battle of fleets \Nin the history of naval warfare
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.19,0:23:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,ended with a one-sided victory for the Japanese side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.69,0:23:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the American convoys \Nin Guadalcanal were left completely intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.58,0:23:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the tremendous effect the steady flow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.82,0:23:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of reinforcements, ammunition, and provisions \Nhad on the ultimate victory in the battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.75,0:23:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one can't help but to question, \Nwas this decision really correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.48,0:23:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When making a decision, one mustn't let \Nconcerns of immediate victory or damage lead him astray, {/get lost/make hesitate}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.64,0:23:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead, he should be concerned with future prospects, \Nnever losing sight of the overall picture at hand. {/picture}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.72,0:23:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This naval battle let the Japanese side bask in glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.27,0:23:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,However, before long, it'll become one of the major causes \Nof the tragedy that is to befall Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.46,0:24:07.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.18,0:24:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In the skies over the Pacific, \NKato's Falcon Squadron engages in an aerial battle {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tateo_Kat%C5%8D - hayabusa is a nickname, means falcon, if I'm getting it right, it's more attached to the squadron/plane than to kato himself}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.35,0:24:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that would later be renowned as miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.57,0:24:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They seize their chance thanks to some prompt decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.85,0:24:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and display glorious team work \Nwith their Army Type 1 Falcon Fighters, {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nakajima_Ki-43_Hayabusa - if you opt out for hayabusa instead of falcon, replace with "Nakajima Ki-43 Hayabusa"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.93,0:24:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,paving the way for the {constant }success \Nof the Japanese army's operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.44,0:24:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The feats of the Kato's Falcon Squadron commander, \Nwho was as free as the wind, {no clue what he means by "freely; right and left; as one pleases​ activity/actions"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.60,0:24:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way until his tragic death in the Bay of Bengal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.74,0:24:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will be depicted in the next episode of Decision: \NKato's Falcon Squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.70,0:24:38.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,700)}Episode 14 \NKato's Falcon Squadron {加藤隼戦闘隊}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.00,0:24:47.56,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.56,0:24:51.90,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.90,0:24:56.26,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.26,0:25:04.83,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.83,0:25:13.21,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
